article.headline: Indiana 100, Northwestern St. 66
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Verdell Jones scored 24 points and Christian Watford added 17 to lead Indiana to a 100-66 win over Northwestern State on Friday night. The Hoosiers, who are 6-0 for the first time since 2002, started the second half with a 12-3 run. Devon Baker scored 24 points for Northwestern State (3-3), which came into Friday averaging 86 points a game. But Indiana held the Demons to 35.1-percent shooting. The teams combined for 22 fouls in the first half. The Hoosiers hit 8 of 11 free throws to take a 38-30 lead into halftime.
